gameRecap.title: Game Recap: 76ers 133, Spurs 126
gameRecap.excerpt: The 76ers defeated the Spurs, 133-126 in a double-overtime thriller. Tyrese Maxey led Philadelphia with a career-high 52 points, along with five rebounds, and seven assists. Victor Wembanyama totaled 33 points, 18 rebounds, seven blocks, six assists, and five 3PM for San Antonio in the loss. The 76ers win their fifth in a row as they move to 44-35 while the Spurs move to 19-59.
